WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.900 --> 00:00:06.390
It's easy to create a text track effect by
using Title 3D within Final Cut Pro.

00:00:06.390 --> 00:00:12.620
To do this, navigate to the generators menu
and select Boris - Title 3D.

00:00:12.620 --> 00:00:15.999
Then click on the controls tab within the
Viewer window.

00:00:15.999 --> 00:00:21.320
Click where it says click for options to launch
the Title 3D window.

00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:27.419
Go ahead and type your title and then press
the apply button when you are finished.

00:00:27.419 --> 00:00:31.480
Now click on the Video tab at the top of the
Viewer window.

00:00:31.480 --> 00:00:36.000
Drag the title into the superimpose area within
the Canvas window.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.930
This will place your title above your background
video in your sequence.

00:00:40.930 --> 00:00:45.380
Next, double click on your title within the
timeline.

00:00:45.380 --> 00:00:49.780
This loads the title back into the Viewer
window.

00:00:49.780 --> 00:00:52.810
Navigate back to the Controls tab at the top
of the Viewer window.

00:00:52.810 --> 00:00:57.920
Lets adjust the viewer window in order to
expand the keyframe area for the controls.

00:00:57.920 --> 00:01:03.370
Scroll down the list of parameters and look
for tracking.

00:01:03.370 --> 00:01:06.620
Go ahead and expand the keyframe area for
the tracking parameter.

00:01:06.620 --> 00:01:15.680
Using the keyboard shortcut Command = or Command
+ to expand the clip area in the keyframe

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:16.680
graph.

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:19.620
Now, park at the front of the clip.

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:25.360
Then adjust this tracking control so the letters
are further apart from each other.

00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:28.500
Press the insert keyframe button.

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:33.840
Now, move the playhead indicator forward a
second or two and then adjust the tracking

00:01:33.840 --> 00:01:37.430
back to zero.

00:01:37.430 --> 00:01:44.860
Okay check it out by pressing the spacebar
to play your sequence.

00:01:44.860 --> 00:01:49.260
For additional effect, you can right click
on each of these keyframes to change them

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:51.659
to smooth.

00:01:51.659 --> 00:01:56.740
This will give you bezier handles that you
can adjust so your effect eases in or eases

00:01:56.740 --> 00:01:58.510
out.

00:01:58.510 --> 00:02:03.490
You can also adjust these handles to create
a curve for the tracking parameter.

00:02:03.490 --> 00:02:07.490
Now check it the difference.

00:02:07.490 --> 00:02:11.329
Finally, you might want to add dissolve at
the beginning of your title.

00:02:11.329 --> 00:02:16.370
You can do this by right clicking at the head
of your title and choosing add dissolve from

00:02:16.370 --> 00:02:18.290
the contextual menu.

00:02:18.290 --> 00:02:20.950
Okay that's it!

